ernational XI.<ref name=\"margin\">[http://stats.espncricinfo.com/nz-1-day-2011/content/records/283281.html Records / Women's One-Day Internationals / Team records / Largest margin of victory (by runs)] \u2013 ESPNcricinfo. Retrieved 31 August 2015.</ref>\n|stack=y }}\n{{Single-innings cricket match collapsible\n| date = 10 January\n| time = \n| team1 = {{crw-rt|NZL|stack=y }}\n| score1 = 147/9 (60 overs)\n| team2 = {{crw|ENG|stack=y }}\n| score2 = 147/8 (60 overs)\n| result = Match tied\n| report = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/41/41934.html Scorecard]\n| venue = [[Cornwall Park Stadium|Cornwall Park]], [[Auckland]]\n| motm =\n| toss = England won the toss and elected to bowl.\n| notes = This match was the first tie in women's ODI matches.<ref name=\"tie\"/>\n|stack=y }}\n{{Single-innings cricket match collapsible\n| date = 12 January\n| time = \n| team1 = {{crw-rt|IND|stack=y }}\n| score1 = 112 (52.2 overs)\n| team2 = {{crw|ENG|stack=y }}\n| score2 = 114/6 (36 overs)\n| result = England won by 4 wickets\n| report = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/41/41942.html Scorecard]\n| venue = [[Cornwall Park Stadium|Cornwall Park]], [[Auckland]]\n| motm =\n| toss = India won the toss and elected to bat.\n|stack=y }}\n{{Single-innings cricket match collapsible\n| date = 12 January\n| time = \n| team1 = {{crw-rt|NZL|stack=y }}\n| score1 = 244/6 (60 overs)\n| team2 = [[File:Flag of None.svg|22px]] [[International XI women's cricket team|International XI]]\n| score2 = 60 (34.4 overs)\n| result = New Zealand won by 184 runs\n| report = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/41/41943.html Scorecard]\n| venue = [[Eden Park]] (No. 2 Oval), [[Auckland]]\n| motm =\n| toss = International XI won the toss and elected to bowl.\n| notes = New Zealand's winning margin set a new record for ODIs, beating Australia's mark that had been set only two days prior. The record was not beaten until the 1988 World Cup.<ref name=\"margin\"/>\n|stack=y }}\n{{Sing